/ooc I made my way to Steamfont Mountains on Saturday morning and parked there until I was able to reach Norrath again on Saturday evening about 11:15pm EST.<br>
<br>
/ic <br>
<br>
I awoke to find Fellowship of the Griffon had gathered in Steamfont Mountains, welcoming former members of Order of the Source into their guild.  There were over 64 adventurers in the Steamfont Mountains.<br>
<br>
One of the people seemingly involved at their celebration found Ambassador Zunk who commanded Meldarith (I'm not sure of the spelling and do not know who this person is) to show the infidels the might of a united Grobb and minotaurs outside of the minotaur caverns.  I suppose the infidels were the other races of Norrath.<br>
<br>
I made my way to the minotaur caverns but all I could see was Ambassador Zunk -- no other trolls and no other adventurers.  I could hear them though.  Some new people were shouting to find out what was happening, other people were shouting about leewt.  In time, others were giving % health status of Ambassador Zunk.  The entire time, the first person that found Ambassador Zunk was saying he should get the lewt from him.<br>
<br>
Though the other adventurers were welcoming everyone to help defeat the Trolls, I stood by, watching Ambassador Zunk.  Pondering my next course of action, I decided that this behavior was simply unbecoming of a MacLear.  I turned away and headed to the Ak'Anon entrance.  <br>
<br>
It is at the Ak'Anon entrance that I write this entry.  I've learned a very important lesson this evening. *~*<br>
<br>
/ooc I will never, ever again post a GM sponsored event unless it is something like the undead in Norrath around Halloween or I have a lot more details.  I was really disappointed in this and apologize to Naylin, Brecklin and the others that made the trip to Steamfont.  Please accept my humble apologies. <p><a href="//home.attbi.com/~geist22/lanadena2.jpg"><center>
<img src="//home.attbi.com/~geist22/lanadena2.jpg" border="0">
</a> 

