<br>
/ooc <br>
Still, sister...twas nobody's fault for our own disappointment, which was more because we missed the event itself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  We've never been present for a GM event ourselves  and if they will be a lot like this one you describe, I no longer have much desire to do so.  I'll stick with those events created by MacLear, our allies, and our enemies. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ravnanger>Ravnanger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Shaman and Noble</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#330000>(2/10/02 12:30:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=87.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trolls!  Trolls I tell you!</span><hr size=1> At least I got to see the Steamfont mountains. I had not been there since my youth. I was there scouting when I found a cave filled with minotaurs. Seems they don't like intruders and showed me so.  After a hasty exit on my part I was running across the hills and found a nice cliff. It had a wonderful view of the Mountains, looking south to Akanon. Of course being blessed with the spirits of the wolf......Even the soft mosses at the bottom that grow there were not soft enough to land on. <p><a
